    How we work (transparent, QC-first)

    No surprises. You’ll know what’s feasible, what you’ll receive, and how QC is handled—before work starts.

    Send what you have (even if it’s incomplete)

    Dataset + objectives/RQs + deadline + any institute/sponsor template. If you’re unsure, share context—we’ll guide what’s needed.

    • Dataset (Excel/CSV/SPSS/R output)
    • Research questions / objectives
    • Constraints (format, timeline, required tool)

    We review feasibility and share a clear quotation

    We check what’s realistic, what’s risky, and what needs cleaning—then propose the simplest pathway.

    • Feasibility check + recommended pathway
    • Deliverables list (so expectations are clear)
    • Quote + turnaround options

    Work begins after approval + payment

    Once you’re comfortable with the plan and quote, you approve and we start. This keeps the process clean and professional—especially for B2B.

    • Scope confirmation
    • Secure handling + confidentiality
    • Kickoff message with next steps

    Analysis build + reporting structure

    We structure outputs so they’re readable and defensible—not just “run tests and export tables.”

    • Cleaning log + variable mapping
    • Outputs (tables/figures) + interpretation notes
    • “What-to-report” guidance

    QC pass (our differentiator)

    A second set of eyes checks logic and reporting consistency—so you don’t get caught in review with avoidable issues.

    • Objectives ↔ variables ↔ test alignment
    • Sanity checks (missing/outliers handled transparently)
    • Interpretation discipline (no overclaiming)
    • Table/figure consistency + labeling

    Delivery + revisions

    You receive files + notes. Then we refine based on your feedback (and supervisor comments, if you share them).

    • Editable outputs + explanation notes
    • Revision rounds as per package
    • Final checklist (what’s done + what’s pending)

    FAQ

    Straight answers—so you can decide quickly.

    What are data analysis services for research?
    Our data analysis services focus on making your analysis choices and results clear: data readiness, test pathway, editable outputs, and interpretation notes you can explain confidently.
    Do you support thesis, dissertation, and PhD data analysis services?
    Yes—this includes thesis data analysis services, dissertation data analysis services, and phd data analysis services where you need defensible logic and clean reporting.
    Do you provide SPSS data analysis services and R Studio data analysis?
    Yes. We offer spss data analysis services and r studio data analysis, plus practical spss help to understand outputs.
    Can you help with questionnaire data analysis and Likert scale analysis?
    Yes—questionnaire data analysis, survey data analysis services, and likert scale analysis are common. We also support reliability checks including reliability analysis cronbach alpha when relevant.
    Do you support regression analysis help and multiple regression analysis?
    Yes. We provide regression analysis help including multiple regression analysis when it matches your design and assumptions.
    Do you handle messy data? (missing values / outliers)
    Yes—our data cleaning services are transparent and logged. We tell you what was changed and why, so reporting remains defendable.
    Can you support clinical research data analysis, public health data analysis, or biostatistics?
    Yes—clinical research data analysis, public health data analysis, and biostatistics consulting services are supported with disciplined reporting and QC checks.
    Do you fabricate results or make claims for clients?
    No. Integrity-first: we don’t fabricate data, results, or claims. We focus on clarity, defensibility, and reporting structure so you can present your work responsibly.
